            <span class="block">Your Gallery Books</span>
            <span class="block text-pink-300 mt-3">More</span>
            <span class="block text-white mt-3">Appointments</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal story -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-300/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Hair stylist friend complained: "I'm talented but fully booked only 3 days/week." Checked website: text-only service list, no photos of work, "call to book" only. Competitor down the street: beautiful photo gallery, online booking, testimonials. Fully booked 6 days/week. In beauty business, seeing is believing. Your work = your marketing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Key stats -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 pt-6">
            <div class="bg-white/5 border-[2px] border-white/10 p-4 backdrop-blur-sm">
              <div class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-[#EC4899]">3x</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 font-medium">More bookings with gallery</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/5 border-[2px] border-white/10 p-4 backdrop-blur-sm">
              <div class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-[#EC4899]">67%</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 font-medium">Fewer inquiries without photos</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/5 border-[2px] border-white/10 p-4 backdrop-blur-sm">
              <div class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-[#EC4899]">23</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 font-medium">Missed calls/day without booking</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white/5 border-[2px] border-white/10 p-4 backdrop-blur-sm">
              <div class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-[#EC4899]">5x</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1 font-medium">More consults with before/after</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: Stylist Emma's Transformation -->
  <section class="bg-white py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">
          MY EXPERIENCE: Text-Only Site â†’ Fully Booked
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">11 months tracking salon website transformations</p>

        <!-- THE BEFORE -->
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#EC4899] pl-5 py-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#EC4899] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Hair stylist Emma charged $85 for cuts, $150+ for color. Great work, 8 years experience. Her website? Generic Squarespace template with text-only service list, no photos of her work, "call for booking" only. Fully booked 3 days/week maximum. Competitor down street with photo gallery and online booking: fully booked 6 days/week. Same prices. Emma couldn't understand why she struggled to fill chairs.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE FIX -->
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#EC4899] pl-5 py-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#EC4899] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Complete redesign in Framer with custom gallery layout. Added 180+ photos: haircuts, balayage, highlights, color corrections, bridal styles, treatments. Before/after photos with client consent (always get consent). Added stylist bio: "8 years experience, specializes in balayage and color correction." Listed all prices transparently. Integrated Calendly for online booking. Added testimonials with real client photos. Launched Instagram feed integration.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE AFTER -->
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#EC4899] pl-5 py-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-r mb-6">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#EC4899] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Week 1: 47 online bookings, only 19 missed calls (captured 71% of bookings that would have been lost). Month 1: booking inquiries 3-4/day â†’ 12/day (+200%), new client bookings up 183%, fully booked 5 days/week. Month 2: hired assistant stylist, waitlist for Saturdays. Month 4: expanded to second chair, revenue $18K/month (up from $9K). Month 6: raised prices to $95 cuts, $175+ color. No drop in bookings. Clients pay for proof of skill.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN -->
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#EC4899] pl-5 py-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#EC4899] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Month 1:</strong> Framer site launched with 180-photo gallery. Before/after photos added. Calendly booking integrated. Transparent pricing page. Week 1: 47 online bookings, 19 missed calls (previously 23 missed calls/day, zero captured). Booking inquiries: 3-4/day â†’ 12/day (+200%). New client bookings up 183%. Fully booked 5 days/week (was 3). Revenue $11,200 (up from $9,000). Client feedback: "Your photos proved you know what you're doing."</li>
            <li><strong>Month 2:</strong> Added Instagram feed integration to gallery. Hired assistant stylist (took overflow). Waitlist for Saturdays. Raised color prices 10%. No drop in bookings. 27 online bookings/week average. Revenue $14,300. Started bridal portfolio section. 3 bridal consultations booked from website alone.</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3:</strong> Expanded to second chair. Full waitlist for new clients. Blog launched: "Color Correction Guide," "Balayage vs Highlights." SEO traffic generating 12 leads/week. Email list 423 subscribers. Revenue $18,400 (doubled in 90 days). Plans for second location in 6 months.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH: 6 Salon Website Lies -->
  <section class="bg-gray-50 py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">
          THE HARD TRUTH: 6 Salon Website Lies
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Common myths that cost stylists bookings every single day</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"No photos protects my work"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: No photos = "what if they mess up my hair?" Emma's text-only site: 3-4 booking inquiries/day. 180-photo gallery: 12 inquiries/day (+200%). Photos reduce risk perception. No photos increase fear. In beauty business, seeing is believing. Hide your work, lose bookings.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Phone booking builds personal connection"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: Phone booking = missed calls. Emma averaged 23 missed calls/day while working. Added Calendly: 47 online bookings week 1, only 19 missed calls. Captured 71% of bookings that would have been lost. Online booking = 24/7 receptionist. Personal connection happens IN the chair, not ON the phone.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"No prices filters out cheap clients"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: No prices filters out EVERYONE. Staff spent 3 hours/day answering "how much for highlights?" Emma added transparent pricing: phone calls dropped 67%, bookings increased 23%. Serious clients know your value. Price shoppers self-filter. Everyone's time saved.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Stylist bios don't matter"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: Clients choose stylists, not salons. Emma added bio: "8 years experience, specializes in balayage and color correction." New client bookings up 38% month 1. People want to know: who is cutting my hair? What's their experience? Humanize your team or lose bookings to salons that do.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Before/after photos are tacky"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: Before/after = most powerful beauty marketing. Emma added before/after photos: consultation bookings increased 5x. Words claim "great color correction." Photos SHOW great color correction. Tacky? No. Proof. Always get client consent. Professional presentation. But show the work.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-[2px] border-gray-200 p-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">âœ•</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Social media replaces website"</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Truth: Instagram + website work together. Emma added Instagram feed to website: cross-pollination increased bookings 27%. Website = permanent portfolio + booking. Social = discovery + engagement. Need both. Website captures referrals, Google search, walk-ins who check later. Social drives awareness. Build both.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
